An internal report produced by theBelgian National Bank foresees the country's gross nationalproduct growth falling in 1987 to 1.0 pct from 2.3 pct in 1986,the independent newspaper Le Soir said.    A National Bank spokesman said the newspaper article wasbasically correct, but that the report was produced six weeksago and figures were therefore to some extent out of date.    The government's planning bureau predicted growth of 0.9pct this year in a study published last month. REUTER&#3;